cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it discusses the effectiveness of a method for measuring similarity between binary byte sequences for digital forensics. It could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new method for hashing and comparing data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with similarity measures for files. It may also fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses the development of a high-performance implementation of the method. Finally, it could be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it specifically mentions the implementation being in Java.
